On 1/25/05 6:52 PM, "Greg Potts" <Greg(-at-)pottsfamily.ca> wrote:

> 
> My suggestion:
> Drop the engine, check the end play, and have a leak down test done.
> This will tell you about the current condition of the rings and bottom
      end without getting in too deep.

Greg,

The leakdown will tell you good info for sure, but checking end play will
not tell you much about the bottom end. Type 4 engines do not wear heavily
on the thrust bearing, so the end play can be fine and the bottom end can
still be garbage.

